  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>

        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="AN143.1-kilavi"><app><lem>tōḻi talaimakaḷa tāṟṟāmai kaṇṭu talaimakaṉ celavaḻuṅkac colliyatu</lem><rdg wit="#C9v #RK">poruḷvayiṟ piriyakkarutiya talaimakaṉait tōḻicelavaḻuṅkuvittatu</rdg><rdg wit="#C7">tōḻi talaimakaḷa tāṟṟāmai kaṇṭu ceṉṟu poruḷavayiṟ piriyak karutiya talaimakaṉaic celavaḻuṅkuvittatu</rdg></app>.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en">What the confidante, seeing HER lack of strength, said to HIM in order to prevent [him] from going.</p>
        </div>
        <div rend="parallel">
            <lg xml:id="AN143.1">
              <l>ceyviṉai pirikka veṇṇik kaimmika</l>
              <l>kāṭukavi ṉoḻiyak kaṭuṅkatir teṟutali</l>
              <l>ṉīṭuciṉai <supplied>vāṭi</supplied>ya vāka volleṉa</l>
              <l>vāṭupal lakalilai kōṭaik koyyun</l>
              <l>tēkkama laṭukkat tāṅkaṇ mēkkāḻpu</l>
              <l>muḷiyariṟ piṟanta vaḷivaḷar kūreric</l>
              <l>cuṭarnimir neṭuṅkoṭi viṭarmukai muḻaṅkum</l>
              <l>vemmuṉai yaruñcura nīnti yaiya</l>
              <l>cēṟu meṉṟa ciṟucoṟ kivaṭkē</l>
              <l>vacaiyil vempōr <supplied>vā</supplied>ṉavaṉ maṟava</l>
              <l>ṉacaiyiṉ vāḻnarkku naṉkalañ curakkum</l>
              <l>poyyā vāyvāṭ puṉaika<supplied>ḻa</supplied>ṟ piṭṭaṉ</l>
              <l>maitava ḻuyarcimaik kutiraik kavā<supplied>a</supplied></l>
              <l>ṉakaṉṟa neṭuñcuṉait tuvalaiyiṉ malarnta</l>
              <l>taṇkamaḻ nīlam pōlak</l>
              <l>kaṇpaṉi kaluḻntaṉa nōkō yāṉē.</l>
            </lg>
            <lg xml:lang="en">
                <l>Thinking to part [from her] for the work to be done, (1a-c)</l>
                <l>there on the mountain side dense with teak trees, (5a-c)</l>
                <l>where the many moving/fading wide leaves are carried to the Kōṭai hill (4)</l>
                <l>noisily, so that the long branches will be dried up, (3)</l>
                <l>because of the fierce [sun] rays’ excessive scorching, so that the wild forest’s beauty comes to an end, (1df.)</l>
                <l>crossing the difficult desert on the hot frontier, o lord, (8)</l>
                <l>where, sinking from the heights, the glowing outstretched long banners of sharp flames</l>
                <l>growing in the wind, which were born from the dry thicket, thunder in cleft caves, (5d-7)</l>
                <l>because of those little words, “we will go”, as for her, (9)</l>
                <l>[her] eyes, (16a)</l>
                <l rend="indent4">like cool fragrant blue lotuses (15)</l>
                <l rend="indent4">that bloomed in the droplets from the vast mountain pools that opened (14)</l>
                <l rend="indent4">in the Kutirai slope with cloud-covered high peaks (13)</l>
                <l rend="indent4">of Pittaṉ, with a sword [and] ornate anklets, [whose] mouth does not lie,</l>
                <l rend="indent4">the bold man of the Cēra king of flawless hot battle,</l>
                <l rend="indent4">who lovingly showers good ornaments on those who live, (10-12)</l>
                <l>have dimmed with tears. Ah, I ache. (16)</l>
            </lg>
        </div>
    </body>
  </text>
